    "image_with_text_k9G6MM": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "caption_bx378Y": {
          "type": "caption",
          "settings": {
            "caption": "How Everyone",
            "text_style": "subtitle",
            "text_size": "medium"
          }
        },
        "heading_HE7NJF": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can Help",
            "heading_size": "h3"
          }
        },
        "text_9eEfQc": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>But we're committed to doing more than mattress donations to build a better future for kids, and, there's something you can do to help. Roughly 15 to 20 million mattresses and box springs go to landfills every year in the US, which is a terrible waste when there are so many children in need of a quality kids mattress. By donating or recycling your child's used mattress, you can help to reduce the waste and help more kids get a great mattress.<\/p>\n<h4>An Old Mattress for a Better Future<\/h4>\n<p>Donating or recycling your child's used mattress keeps it out of a landfill, and you may even be improving the life of a child in need.<\/p>\n<h4>How to Donate a Mattress<\/h4>\n<p>Donating a gently-used mattress is easy. Visit DonationTown.com and look through a list of trustworthy, screened charities in need of mattress donations in your area - chances are, many will happily pick up the mattress for you.<\/p>\n<h4>How to Recycle a Mattress<\/h4>\n<p>Another option is recycling. Simply find a mattress recycling center by visiting the Mattress Recycling Center Locator on earth911.com, load up your mattress, and take it over.<\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
